Implemented a real scoped-token/server-enforcement slice of the `happy-sync` refactor.

The server now mints and validates SyncNode claims instead of treating “session-scoped” as client-side metadata. I added claim parsing/helpers in [syncNodeToken.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/auth/syncNodeToken.ts#L1), attached parsed claims during auth in [enableAuthentication.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/api/utils/enableAuthentication.ts#L6), enforced them on Socket.IO connections in [socket.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/api/socket.ts#L66), and locked session lifecycle/message routes to account scope vs per-session access in [sessionRoutes.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/api/routes/sessionRoutes.ts#L41) and [v3SessionRoutes.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/api/routes/v3SessionRoutes.ts#L52). There is also a new server route to mint a session-scoped token at [sessionRoutes.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/api/routes/sessionRoutes.ts#L360), and the daemon wrapper now uses that path in [packages/happy-cli/src/daemon/syncNode.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-cli/src/daemon/syncNode.ts#L89).

I updated coverage so Level 1 uses real server-minted session tokens and explicitly checks server-side rejection paths in [packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.integration.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.integration.test.ts#L54), and fixed the server route mock drift in [v3SessionRoutes.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/api/routes/v3SessionRoutes.test.ts#L162).

Verified with:
- `yarn workspace happy-server build`
- `yarn workspace happy-server test sources/app/api/routes/v3SessionRoutes.test.ts`
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:unit`
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:integration`
- `yarn workspace happy-coder typecheck`

The repo is still not at full spec completion. The major remaining gaps are the same ones identified during audit: CLI/app still have legacy sync paths, `ApiSessionClient` is still central, and `happy-agent`/old reducer code have not been removed yet.
